# Data Dictionary

## 1. Overview

This document describes the main fields used in the structured data layer of the project.

The project combines simplified indicators from:

1. MapBiomas
2. INPE / TerraBrasilis / PRODES

The main structured output is a municipality-year environmental panel.

Main output files:

```text
data/processed/municipality_environmental_panel.parquet
data/processed/municipality_environmental_panel_scored.parquet
```

The structured panel supports the RAG system by providing numerical evidence for environmental screening summaries.

---

## 2. Main Analytical Unit

The main analytical unit is:

```text
municipality-year
```

This means each row represents one municipality in one reference year.

Example:

```text
Municipality: Sinop
State: MT
Biome: Amazon
Year: 2024
```

This level of aggregation is useful for a first version because it is simple, explainable and compatible with both MapBiomas and INPE / PRODES indicators.

---

## 3. Identification Columns

| Column | Type | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|---|
| `municipality_code` | string | Official municipality identifier used to merge MapBiomas and INPE tables | `5107909` |
| `municipality_name` | string | Municipality name | `Sinop` |
| `state` | string | Brazilian state abbreviation | `MT` |
| `biome` | string | Main biome associated with the municipality or record | `Amazon` |
| `year` | integer | Reference year of the observation | `2024` |

### Notes

- `municipality_code` should be treated as a string to avoid merge problems caused by leading zeros or numeric formatting.
- `year` should be treated as an integer.
- The biome field may require careful interpretation because some municipalities can intersect more than one biome.

