## 7. Derived Environmental Indicators

These indicators are generated by the risk scoring pipeline.

Module:

```text
src/agro_rag/structured/risk_score.py
```

Output file:

```text
data/processed/municipality_environmental_panel_scored.parquet
```

---

### 7.1 Native Vegetation Loss

| Column | Type | Unit | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `mapbiomas_native_vegetation_loss_ha` | float | hectares | Year-to-year reduction in native vegetation area |

Calculation logic:

```text
previous_year_native_vegetation_area
-
current_year_native_vegetation_area
```

If the result is negative, it is clipped to zero.

Interpretation:

```text
Higher values indicate greater reduction in native vegetation compared with the previous year.
```

Important limitation:

```text
Native vegetation loss is an environmental screening signal, not a legal conclusion.
```

---

### 7.2 Agriculture or Pasture Expansion

| Column | Type | Unit | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `mapbiomas_agriculture_or_pasture_expansion_ha` | float | hectares | Year-to-year increase in agriculture plus pasture area |

Calculation logic:

```text
current_year_agriculture_area + current_year_pasture_area
-
previous_year_agriculture_area - previous_year_pasture_area
```

Equivalent conceptual form:

```text
current_year_agriculture_plus_pasture
-
previous_year_agriculture_plus_pasture
```

If the result is negative, it is clipped to zero.

Interpretation:

```text
Higher values indicate expansion of agriculture and/or pasture area compared with the previous year.
```

Important limitation:

```text
Agriculture or pasture expansion does not automatically imply illegal deforestation.
```

