## 8. Normalized Score Components

The risk scoring pipeline applies min-max normalization to selected indicators.

Min-max normalization:

```text
normalized_value =
    (value - minimum_value)
    /
    (maximum_value - minimum_value)
```

The normalized values range from 0 to 1.

Generated columns:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| `inpe_prodes_deforestation_area_ha_normalized` | Normalized INPE / PRODES deforestation component |
| `mapbiomas_native_vegetation_loss_ha_normalized` | Normalized native vegetation loss component |
| `mapbiomas_agriculture_or_pasture_expansion_ha_normalized` | Normalized agriculture/pasture expansion component |

### Important note

Normalization is calculated over the available dataset. Therefore, the score is relative to the records included in the current analysis.

If the dataset changes, normalized values and scores may also change.

---

## 9. Environmental Risk Score

| Column | Type | Range | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `environmental_risk_score` | float | 0 to 1 | Explainable environmental screening score |

Default formula:

```text
environmental_risk_score =
    0.50 * normalized_inpe_prodes_deforestation_area_ha
  + 0.30 * normalized_mapbiomas_native_vegetation_loss_ha
  + 0.20 * normalized_mapbiomas_agriculture_or_pasture_expansion_ha
```

### Interpretation

The score is used to prioritize municipality-year records for deeper review.

| Score Meaning | Interpretation |
|---|---|
| Higher score | Stronger environmental screening signal |
| Lower score | Weaker environmental screening signal within the analyzed dataset |

### Critical limitation

The score is not:

- proof of illegal deforestation;
- proof of environmental crime;
- proof of legal non-compliance;
- final ESG classification;
- regulatory conclusion.

It is only an analytical screening indicator.

---

## 10. Environmental Risk Class

| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `environmental_risk_class` | string | Categorical interpretation of the environmental risk score |

Default classification:

| Score Range | Class |
|---|---|
| 0.00 to 0.33 | `Low` |
| 0.34 to 0.66 | `Medium` |
| 0.67 to 1.00 | `High` |

### Interpretation

| Class | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `Low` | Lower environmental screening signal in the current dataset |
| `Medium` | Intermediate environmental screening signal |
| `High` | Higher environmental screening signal and stronger candidate for deeper review |

### Important limitation

A `High` class does not prove illegal deforestation.  
A `Low` class does not guarantee absence of environmental risk.

